)|publisher=Filmreference.com|year=2010|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/11/Polly-Holliday.html|accessdate=2010-11-17}}</ref>\n*  1937   &ndash; [[Richard Petty]], American race car driver and sportscaster\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[David Owen]], English physician and politician, [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs]]\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Alexandros Panagoulis]], Greek poet and politician (d. 1976)\n*  1939   &ndash; [[John H. Sununu]], American engineer and politician, 14th [[White House Chief of Staff]]\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Paul Williams (The Temptations)|Paul Williams]], American singer and choreographer (d. 1973)\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Kenneth Clarke]], English politician, [[Lord Chancellor|Lord High Chancellor of Great Britain]]\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[William Guest (singer)|William Guest]], American singer-songwriter and producer (d. 2015) \n*  1941   &ndash; [[Wendell Mottley]], Trinidadian sprinter, economist, and politician\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[John Eekelaar]], South African-English lawyer and scholar\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Vicente Fox]], Mexican businessman and politician, 35th [[President of Mexico]] (2000-2006)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buscabiografias.com/biografia/verDetalle/3690/Vicente%20Fox%20Quesada|title=Vicente Fox Quesada|publisher=Busca Biografias|language=Spanish|accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Ivi Eenmaa]], Estonian politician, 36th [[Mayor of Tallinn]]\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Larry Lake (musician)|Larry Lake]], American-Canadian trumpet player and composer (d. 2013)\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Richard Axel]], American neuroscientist and biologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Ron Silver]], American actor, director, and political activist (d. 2009)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Larry David]], American actor, comedian, producer, and screenwriter<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/larry-david/bio/180721|title=Larry David Biography|magazine=[[TV G