ha Shneider]], Russian-American singer, keyboard player, and actress (b. 1956)\n*  2008   &ndash; [[Elizabeth Spriggs]], English actress and screenwriter (b. 1929)\n*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Beryl Bainbridge]], English screenwriter and author (b. 1932)\n*[[2011]] &ndash; [[Itamar Franco]], Brazilian engineer and politician, 33rd [[President of Brazil]] (b. 1930)\n*[[2012]] &ndash; [[Maurice Chevit]], French actor and screenwriter (b. 1923)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Julian Goodman]], American journalist (b. 1922)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Angelo Mangiarotti]], Italian architect and academic (b. 1921)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Betty Meggers]], American archaeologist and academic (b. 1921)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Ed Stroud]], American baseball player (b. 1939)\n*[[2013]] &ndash; [[Anthony G. Bosco]], American bishop (b. 1927)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Douglas Engelbart]], American computer scientist, invented the [[mouse (computing)|computer mouse]] (b. 1925)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Armand Gaudreault]], Canadian ice hockey player (b. 1921)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Anthony Llewellyn]], Welsh-American chemist, academic, and astronaut (b. 1933)\n*[[2014]] &ndash; [[Emilio \u00c1lvarez Montalv\u00e1n]], Nicaraguan ophthalmologist and politician (b. 1919)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Manuel Cardona]], Spanish physicist and academic (b. 1934)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Mary Innes-Ker, Duchess of Roxburghe]] (b. 1915)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Harold W. Kuhn]], American mathematician and academic (b. 1925)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[Louis Zamperini]], American runner and World War II [[United States Army Air Forces|US Army Air Forces]] captain (b. 1917)\n*[[2015]] &ndash; [[Ronald Davison]], New Zealand lawyer and judge, 10th [[Chief Justice of New Zealand]] (b. 1920) \n*  2015   &ndash; [[Charlie Sanders]], American football player and sportscaster (b. 1946)\n*  2015   &ndash; [[Jim Weaver (athletic director)|Jim Weaver]], American football player and coach (b. 1945)\n*  2015   &ndash; [[Jacobo Zabludovsky]], Mexican journalist (b. 1928)\n*[[2016]] &ndash; [[Caroline Aherne]], English actress and comedian (b. 1963)\n*  2016   &ndash; [[Michael Cimino]], American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1939)\n*  2016   &ndash; [[Patrick Manning]], 4th & 6th Prime Minister of Trinidad and Tobago (b. 1946)\n*  2016   &ndash; [[Elie Wiesel]], Holocaust survivor, activist, and author (b. 1928)\n<!--Do not add people without Wikipedia articles to this list. They will be removed. Do not trust \"this year in history\" websites for accurate date information. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence.-->\n\n==Holidays and observances==\n*Christian [[feast day]]:\n**[[Aberoh and Atom]] ([[Coptic Church]])\n**[[Bernardino Realino]]\n**Feast of the [[Visitation (Christianity)|Visitation]] ([[Anglicanism]]; [[Levo\u010da]] at [[Mari\u00e1nska hora]])\n**[[Monegundis]]\n**[[Otto of Bamberg]]\n**[[Oudoceus]]\n**[[Martinian and Processus]]\n**[[Pishoy]] (Coptic Church)\n**[[Stephen III of Moldavia]]\n**[[July 2 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)]]\n*Earliest day on which [[Public holidays in Zambia|Unity Day]] can fall, while July 8 is the latest; celebrated on Tuesday following [[Heroes' Day#Heroes.27 Day in Zambia|Heroes' Day]]. ([[Zambia]])\n*[[Flag Day (Cura\u00e7ao)]] \n*[[Palio di Siena|Palio di Provenzano]] ([[Siena]], [[Italy]])\n*[[Police Day (Azerbaijan)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n*[http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/july/2 BBC: On This Day]\n*{{NYT On this day|month=07|day=02}}\n*[https://archive.is/20121210205918/http://www1.sympatico.ca/cgi-bin/on_this_day?mth=Jul&day=02 On This Day in Canada]\n\n{{months}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:July 02}}\n[[Category:Days of the year]]\n[[Category:July]]\n", "name_user": "Metallurgist", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEvents", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/July_2"}
